E7_Primitive_streak_and_adjacent_ectoder: Self, with an additional edge back to epiblast (weight 0.24) that is likely explained by the continuous relationship between the ectoderm around the primitive streak and the remainder of the epiblast.

E7_Mixed_mesoderm: The cell state that we annotate as mixed mesoderm, the annotation applied to it by Pijuan-Sala et al. (2019) (PMID 30787436), is inferred to arise from nascent mesoderm.
E7_Anterior_primitive_streak: The anterior primitive streak is well-established to arise from the primitive streak. See PMID 10611967
E7_Primordial_germ_cells: Primordial germ cells (PGCs) are well-established to arise at the posterior primitive streak. See PMID 23125014.
E725_Definitive_endoderm: The definitive endoderm is well-established to arise from the anterior primitive streak. See PMID 10611967
E725_Notochord: The notochord is well-established to arise from the anterior primitive streak. See PMID 26845388
E725_Blood_progenitors: Blood progenitors, presumably primitive at this stage, are well established to arise from hematoendothelial progenitors. Nomenclature from original study (PMID 30787436)
E725_Amniochorionic_mesoderm: Amniochorionic mesoderm (tentative label; these cells called mesenchyme by PMID 30787436) appears to arise from mixed mesoderm.
E725_Mixed_mesoderm: Self, with an additional edge back to nascent mesoderm (weight 0.24) that reflects an established relationship and could be explained by ongoing differentiation or a continuum
E7_Parietal_endoderm: Manually curated "self" connection between E6.75 parietal trophoectoderm (dummy node) and E7.0 parietal endoderm. See text for justification.
E75_Amniochorionic_mesoderm: Self, with an additional edge back to mixed mesoderm (weight 0.29) that reflects an established relationship and could be explained by ongoing differentiation or a continuum
E75_Definitive_endoderm: Self, with an additional edge back to anterior primitive streak (weight 0.30) that reflects an established relationship and could be explained by ongoing differentiation or a continuum
E75_Gut: Gut is well-established to arise from definitive endoderm. See PMID 10611967
E75_Blood_progenitors: Self, with an additional edge back to hematoendothelial progenitors (weight 0.28) that reflects an established relationship and could be explained by ongoing differentiation or a continuum
E75_Rostral_neuroectoderm: Rostral neuroectoderm has edges surpassing threshold back to epiblast (0.53) and primitive streak and adjacent ectoderm (0.47). See PMID 29109536.
E75_Extraembryonic_mesoderm: Extraembryonic mesoderm appears to arise from mixed mesoderm. Note that although this cell state is related to allantois at next timepoint, in general, distinction from other mesodermal cell populations is challenging. See PMID 22855605.
E75_Mixed_mesoderm: Self, but with higher scoring edge back to nascent mesoderm (weight 0.68) that reflects an established relationship and could be explained by ongoing differentiation or incomplete separation.
E75_Splanchnic_mesoderm: Splanchnic mesoderm has edges surpassing threshold back to both nascent (0.61) and mixed (0.39) mesoderm. See PMID 16304598.
E75_Paraxial_mesoderm_A: Paraxial mesoderm A appears to arise from the nascent mesoderm. Distinguished from other paraxial mesoderm cell states based on markers Tbx1, Pax3, and potentially corresponds to anterior paraxial mesoderm. See PMID 23081715, PMID 20692252. Paraxial mesoderm ABC appears to correspond to rostral > caudal gradient.
E75_Paraxial_mesoderm_B: Paraxial mesoderm B appears to arise from the nascent mesoderm. Distinguished from other paraxial mesoderm cell states based on markers Tbx6, Dll1, and potentially corresponds to posterior paraxial mesoderm. See PMID 15986483, PMID 20692252. Paraxial mesoderm ABC appears to correspond to rostral > caudal gradient
E75_Caudal_lateral_epiblast: Caudal lateral epiblast appears to arise from primitive streak and adjacent ectoderm, marked by Nkx1-2 aka Sax1. See https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/045872v1.
E75_Caudal_neuroectoderm: Caudal neuroectoderm appears to arise from primitive streak and adjacent ectoderm. See PMID 11748135.
E75_Surface_ectoderm: Surface ectoderm appears to emerge from primitive streak and adjacent ectoderm. May reflect that primitive streak and adjacent ectoderm comprises a substantial region, as caudal neuroectoderm and caudal lateral epiblast also have edges back to primitive streak and adjacent ectoderm, while epiblast associated with rostral neuroectoderm. See PMID 26690418.
E775_Primitive_erythroid_cells: Primitive erythroid cells are well-established to emerge from blood progenitors. See PMID 24478716.
E775_Paraxial_mesoderm_C: Paraxial mesoderm C emerges with edges back to both nascent mesoderm (0.69) and caudal lateral epiblast (0.27). See https://www.biorxiv.org/content/10.1101/045872v1. Paraxial mesoderm ABC appears to correspond to rostral > caudal gradient
E775_Caudal_neuroectoderm: Self, but with higher scoring edge back to rostral neuroectoderm (weight 0.57) that is likely explained by a continuous relationship.
E775_Gut: Self, but with higher scoring edge back to definitive endoderm (weight 0.64) that presumably reflects an ongoing differentiation or a continuous relationship. Minor contribution (0.14) from embryonic visceral endoderm is established example of convergence that falls below 0.2 threshold.

E775_Rostral_neuroectoderm: Self, with an additional edge back to epiblast (weight 0.20) that reflects an established relationship and could be explained by ongoing differentiation or incomplete separation.

E95_Olfactory_epithelium: Olfactory epithelium appears to arise from the placodal area. See PMID 19027001.
E95_Otic_epithelium: Otic epithelium appears to emerge from the placodal area. See PMID 25713536.
